    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-01-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-01-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="4"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d4">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.5/1–2152</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum for the Record, by the Assistant Secretary of State
                        for European Affairs</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PERKINSGW1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Perkins</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-01-23">January 23,
                            1952</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The attached<note n="1" xml:id="d4fn1">In the attachment, not printed, <persName
                            corresp="#p_EDENSA1">Eden</persName> asked the Embassy to approach
                            <persName corresp="#p_ACHESONDG1">Acheson</persName> on the possibility
                        of holding a tripartite meeting in London about Feb. 13 with <persName
                            corresp="#p_ADENAUERK1">Adenauer</persName> invited to join the
                        discussions immediately following the meeting.</note> is an excerpt from a
                    telegram from Mr. <persName corresp="#p_EDENSA1">Eden</persName> which was
                    brought in today by <persName corresp="#p_STEELSC1">Sir Christopher
                        Steel</persName>.</p>
                <p>I remarked that while we would like to go to London, Paris might prove to be
                    necessary because of <gloss target="#t_EDC1">EDC</gloss> activities going on
                    there at that time and because of the possible requirement for Mr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_SCHUMANR1">Schuman</persName>’s presence there.</p>
                <p>I also expressed the view that February 13 and 14 might be a little late and
                    would not give us much time to straighten out any problems between the three of
                    us before meeting with <persName corresp="#p_ADENAUERK1"
                    >Adenauer</persName>.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_STEELSC1">Sir Christopher</persName> expressed general
                    agreement with the above but expressed the fear that Mr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_EDENSA1">Eden</persName>’s schedule was so tight that he could
                    not participate in tripartite conversations before February 13.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PERKINSGW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">George W. Perkins</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
